This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. From Emmanuel Adeyemi, Lokoja Former senate President and a presidential aspirant under the platform of people’s democratic party, Dr Bukola Saraki has said if elected, he would deploy Technology to combat the current security challenges facing the country and put an end to it. Fielding questions from newsmen after a meeting with the PDP delegates in Kogi State , Saraki said he has all it takes to become the next president of the nation stressing that he has the solutions to all the teething problems confronting the nation. He stressed that Nigerians are currently going through hunger and agony because the ruling party has woefully failed in fixing the economy, securing lives and properties of citizens and providing necessary infrastructure for the citizens If elected, he said he will give priority to the completion of Ajaokuta-steel company so as to boost the economy and create jobs for the teeming youths saying no serious government will neglect such gigantic project. The presidential aspirant who said he has enough experience to rule the country having been a former governor and senate President and has traversed all the nooks and crannies of the nation and know the exact problems confronting each region. According to him , since the beginning of the current democratic settings in 1999 , the north central zone has not been given any opportunity to clinch the presidency adding that the time is now ripe. Saraki also stressed that if elected, he will give equal opportunities to all Nigerians irrespective of tribe and religion to attain the peak in their chosen careers While appealing to the delegates to vote for those who have capacity and really have the love of the common man at heart, he said he was the best among all the contestants and therefore urged them to vote for him in the forthcoming party’s primary.